== Overview == In the text of the ''[[Nihon Shoki]]'' (The Chronicles of Japan), she is said to be the daughter of Omoku, the lord of Isogi Prefecture, while the ''[[Kojiki]]'' (The Records of Ancient Matters) says she was Hosohime, the daughter of Omoku, the founder of Juichi Prefecture.
In the first book of the ''Nihon Shoki'', the empress of Emperor Koryō was Kasuga no Chihayamakahime, and in the second book it was Mashitahime, the ancestor of the Juichi prefectures.
